CONSOLIDATED MEDIA HOLDINGS PTY LIMITED Revenue and Financial Data

   You might say this company concentrates its media assets in Australia. Consolidated Media Holdings (CMH) is a media investment holding company with stakes in Australian television and online services. It owns a 25% stake in FOXTEL, a leading cable-TV operator serving some 1.5 million homes. It also has a 50% stake in Premier Media Group (a joint venture with US-based News Corporation), which operates cable TV channels including a portfolio of FOX Sports outlets and FUEL TV. Billionaire media tycoon James Packer owns about 40% of CMH through Consolidated Press Holdings.
  







